# Supabase CLI — Local Development & Migration Workflow

---

## Install & Initial Setup

```bash
# Install CLI
npm install -g supabase

# Or use npx without installing globally
npx supabase --version

# Login (one-time — opens browser)
supabase login
```

---

## Project Setup (one-time per project)

```bash
# Inside your Rocket project root:

# 1. Initialize Supabase config
supabase init
# Creates: supabase/ folder with config.toml

# 2. Link to your remote Supabase project
supabase link --project-ref [YOUR_PROJECT_REF]
# Prompts for DB password
# Project ref = from your Supabase URL: https://[REF].supabase.co
```

---

## Local Development (Docker)

```bash
# Start local Supabase stack (requires Docker)
supabase start
# Starts: Postgres, PostgREST, Auth, Storage, Studio, Inbucket (local email)
# Takes ~60 seconds first time

# Shows local URLs:
#   API URL:     http://127.0.0.1:54321
#   Studio URL:  http://127.0.0.1:54323   (local dashboard)
#   DB URL:      postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:54322/postgres
#   Anon key:    eyJ...
#   Service key: eyJ...

# Stop
supabase stop

# Check status
supabase status
```

```bash
# .env.local for local development
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=[local anon key from supabase start output]
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=[local service key from supabase start output]
```

