## Type Generation

Always regenerate types after any schema change.

```bash
# Generate TypeScript types from remote schema
supabase gen types typescript --project-ref [REF] > src/types/database.types.ts

# Or from local DB (while supabase start is running)
supabase gen types typescript --local > src/types/database.types.ts
```

```typescript
// src/types/database.types.ts is auto-generated — never edit manually

// Use in your app:
import type { Database } from '@/types/database.types'
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'

const supabase = createClient<Database>(url, key)

// All table names, column names, and types are now autocomplete + type-safe
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('orders')       // ← autocomplete
  .select('id, status') // ← autocomplete
```

```json
// package.json — add type generation script
{
  "scripts": {
    "db:types": "supabase gen types typescript --project-ref [REF] > src/types/database.types.ts",
    "db:diff": "supabase db diff",
    "db:push": "supabase db push",
    "db:reset": "supabase db reset"
  }
}
```

